{"parentUuid":"efc578a5-2edd-4d58-8f89-eafd7459ff4f","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a1f81fe877b9073d0","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01KaAh2C1RZJU8XaLhaZm52Q","toolUseID":"toolu_01KaAh2C1RZJU8XaLhaZm52Q","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:17:36.426Z","uuid":"a47379c7-df9a-4188-86e6-be708e9a75d8","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"03cb5064-e5f1-408e-a863-2dbc52269488","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a1f81fe877b9073d0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KaAh2C1RZJU8XaLhaZm52Q","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Jagat Kalyan Integrity Guardrails\n     2→\n     3→These guardrails make the welfare-ton stack hard to greenwash.\n     4→\n     5→| Rule | Requirement | Failure Mode | Audit Evidence |\n     6→|------|-------------|--------------|----------------|\n     7→| `zero-kills-all` | Any project with zero employment, zero agency, or zero verification scores zero welfare-tons. | High-carbon but extractive projects masquerade as holistic solutions. | Welfare formula, worked examples, and unit tests. |\n     8→| `additionality-bound` | All benchmark carbon values are discounted by an explicit additionality factor, never assumed to be 1.0 by default. | Projects claim carbon that would have happened anyway. | alpha_add parameter in dataset and benchmark outputs. |\n     9→| `verification-three-channel` | Every credible project must specify remote, ground, and ledger/community evidence paths. | Satellite-only or brochure-only claims slip through as 'verified'. | v_sat, v_ground, v_ledger decomposition per benchmark row. |\n    10→| `community-agency` | Community initiation, governance, ownership, and veto power are scored separately. | Buyer-funded projects extract land or labor while claiming social good. | A-factor decomposition and agency rubric. |\n    11→| `worker-fit` | Every benchmark row must name a worker profile and a transition-fit assumption. | Generic 'jobs created' claims with no relation to displaced populations. | worker_profile_id and worker_transition_fit in dataset. |\n    12→| `durability` | All carbon claims are discounted by ecosystem-specific permanence assumptions. | Temporary sequestration sold as durable climate repair. | P-factor decomposition and permanence lookup tables. |\n    13→| `budget-compare` | Every benchmark refresh must compare welfare, carbon, and jobs-only strategies on the same budget. | Cherry-picking the one strategy that flatters the thesis. | PROOF_LATTICE_BENCHMARK.json strategy comparison. |\n    14→| `bounded-claims` | Artifacts must distinguish feasibility-study outputs from production deployment claims. | Reviewer distrust due to startup-scale claims inside a research award. | Proof lattice summary and queue notes. |\n    15→| `non-capture` | Stakeholder pipeline must cover implementers, intermediaries, workforce, policy, and research actors. | A single AI buyer defines the standard and launders legitimacy through the metric. | stakeholder_pipeline.json category coverage. |\n    16→| `provenance` | Every synthetic row must carry a note stating what real-world literature or project family it approximates. | Synthetic scenarios drift into ungrounded fiction. | notes fields in benchmark dataset and references in grant packet. |\n    17→"}]},"uuid":"75aa67e4-1e1d-4949-a7eb-b498da652fa2","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:17:36.426Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"03cb5064-e5f1-408e-a863-2dbc52269488","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
