{"parentUuid":"8497cedf-e2f8-49a6-9aa3-fb2bd710da69","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a1f81fe877b9073d0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015JA8U5RbEHmiCwCNKVj1FB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Autonomous Iteration Queue\n     2→\n     3→- Generated: 2026-03-14T15:34:52.125531+00:00\n     4→- Weakest layer: `institutional`\n     5→\n     6→## Priority Queue\n     7→\n     8→1. Convert the stakeholder requirements tracker into named outreach packets.\n     9→2. Draft 3 stakeholder interview guides and note templates tied to stakeholder_pipeline.json.\n    10→3. Draft 2 letters-of-interest ask templates tied to the benchmark outputs.\n    11→4. After real conversations happen, move 3 stakeholder targets to interviewed status with notes.\n    12→5. Use the benchmark delta table in the grant narrative: welfare optimization preserves more jobs than carbon-only routing.\n    13→\n    14→## Execution Rule\n    15→\n    16→- Prefer actions that produce code, data, tests, or reviewer-facing artifacts.\n    17→- Do not fabricate stakeholder outreach results; advance the tracker honestly.\n    18→- Refresh the proof lattice after each meaningful change.\n    19→"}]},"uuid":"eccf04eb-def9-4b00-b047-2d022c568b6d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:17:55.740Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8497cedf-e2f8-49a6-9aa3-fb2bd710da69","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
